27/06/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- The armed forces killed a Kurdish rebel in eastern Turkey during a security operation, according to media reports Saturday (June 26th). Several other militants from the terrorist Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) were injured, but managed to escape. On Friday, security forces seized 8kg of explosives on a passenger train. One person was detained during that operation in Malatya, eastern Turkey. (AFP, Hurriyet, Anadolu news agency - 26/06/10)
